8
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:45,000
Good morning. My name is Bob Thetteman. I'm the computer technician.

9
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:48,000
Did I call for you last week?

10
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:56,000
Maybe. I work for Alfa maintenance. I imagine someone from your office called our central office and I'm the engineer designated to your case.

11
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:01,000
Yeah, I spoke to a lady there last Tuesday, which is now ten days ago.

12
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:07,000
I made it clear it was an urgent matter and please send someone as soon as possible.

13
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:10,000
Couldn't you or someone else have come sooner?

14
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:15,000
I'm sorry, but I'm not in charge of scheduling all logistics. I simply do not know.

15
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:20,000
All I can tell you is I got the call this week and came as soon as I could.

16
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:26,000
I see. Well, I'll have you know, my manager is rather indignant that it's taking you this long to come.

17
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:33,000
I understand it might not be your fault, but nevertheless you should know what the feeling is around here.

18
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:40,000
I understand, and I'm sorry for any inconvenience. I will try to resolve your computer problem as swiftly and optimally as I can.

19
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:42,000
What and where is the issue?

20
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:49,000
It's this machine right here. It was running slow for a while, I guess, and gradually got worse and worse.

21
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:55,000
Last Tuesday it just stopped working altogether. If you switch it on, you will see what I mean.

22
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:58,000
Okay. Do you know if it's backed up?

23
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,000
Backed up?

24
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:03,000
I mean, do you know if its contents have been copied and saved somewhere else?

25
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:05,000
I don't know.

26
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:08,000
Well, depending on the ensuing operative scenario,

27
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:14,000
if I need to wipe the system directories clean in order to reconfigure default protocols,

28
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:19,000
then my first intervention should be to intricately retrieve all inventories that I can.

29
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:24,000
Otherwise, all data that was stored on its hard drive will be forever lost.

30
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:27,000
My manager would now. Let me go get him.

