00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:48,000
Conversation 2. Have you given more thought to studying law?

37
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:54,000
I've been thinking about it a lot. Yes, in fact, this is why I wished to speak to you.

38
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:57,000
I wanted to hear more about what it's like.

39
00:03:57,000 --> 00:04:00,000
A career in law is a beautiful thing in my opinion.

40
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:04,000
Many people will say it's a boring field, but I disagree.

41
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:08,000
The thing is, there are many different branches of law and many different jobs.

42
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:12,000
You are involved with buildings and construction, right?

43
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:19,000
Correct. I'm a solicitor specializing in real estate. Most of my work involves mediating land disputes.

44
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:23,000
Do you mind giving me an example? Sure.

45
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:28,000
So, in many cases, I am employed to arbitrate between two clashing parties.

46
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:36,000
Let's say, for example, there are two landowners who are in a thorny disagreement about something, like the borders of their adjacent plots.

47
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:40,000
Someone may employ me to break the deadlock and resolve the dispute.

48
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:45,000
Often, my work involves negotiating agreements. Plain and simple.

49
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:50,000
So, you are saying that a lot of what you do is fix people's legal issues.

50
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:56,000
Like, you try to find a solution that benefits everyone and that prevents a problem from escalating.

51
00:04:56,000 --> 00:05:05,000
Exactly. Well put. You need to remember that courts, like all bureaucracies, really, can be very messy for a straighting and expensive.

52
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:10,000
For this reason, it's usually better to resolve problems outside of court whenever possible.

53
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:16,000
I see. So, besides knowing the law inside out, you need good people skills, right?

54
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:21,000
Of course. Any job that involves people requires good interpersonal skills.

55
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:26,000
And any law professional needs to be very eloquent at articulating that argument.

56
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:32,000
Right. So, I've been thinking about studying criminal law. I think it sounds very interesting.

57
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:39,000
Hmm. Yes. I'd say there's more money in property law, but the stakes are higher in criminal law.

58
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:42,000
I can see how you would find it more interesting.

